The paper discusses the phenomenon of filter bubbles and confirmation bias in hashtag usage on Twitter, which is highly related to social media and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also touches upon the social aspects of Twitter and how users interact with each other, which makes cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the categorization and annotation of tweets using hashtags, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze tweets, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
